⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of THE MARKET
node MKT · MKT · ⟦THE MARKET:MKT:fa28a1⟧

WHO   — THE MARKET — a agora sphere
WHAT  — No one sets the price of bread. It emerges — from millions of buyers wanting more when it's cheap and sellers offering more when it's dear, meeting at a number that clears the shelves. The market is a vast, leaderless computer for discovering what things are worth, and a vast, leaderless way for that discovery to go wrong.
WHERE — a sphere of the marketplace  Framework inputs: value; exchange; rivalry; the open question  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — No one sets the price of bread. It emerges — from millions of buyers wanting more when it's cheap and sellers offering more when it's dear, meeting at a number that clears the shelves. The market is a vast, leaderless computer for discovering what things are worth, and a vast, leaderless way for that discovery to go wrong.
HOW   — Crystallized from the public record.

